  "text": "2.1. Vertex operator algebras. In this subsection we briefly review some basic notions and facts in the theory of vertex operator algebras from [CITATION_1] , [FHL] , [FLM] , [LL] and [Z] . Let (V, Y, 1, ω) be a vertex operator algebra as defined in [FLM] (see also [B] ). V is called of CFT type if V = n≥0 V n and dim V 0 = 1.",
